## Proposed Modifications using Unconventional Approaches :   



**Class 'Mini Pool':**     




- **Multimodal Attention**: Implement attention mechanisms between features extracted from different pooling operations ("MAX" & "MIN") instead of simply concatenating them. This allows each feature map element at any position iin space be influenced not only on similar elements but also distant ones across both MAX& MIN pools, leading potential improvements via information sharing among diverse spatial representations generated during separate poolings..






# Class Eve modifications







-- Employ Spatial Transformer Networks (`STNs`) replacing conventional MaxPooling layers used previously; STN architectures leverage transformer networks designed specifically operate over spatially correlated data such images enabling more efficient capture long range dependencies amongst pixels compared traditional convolutions employed currently,.





--- Alternatively,,, incorporate dilated convolution techniques into maxpooling layer implementation allowing wider receptive fields while preserving computational efficiency ; dilation factors control spacing out activation functions thereby increasing effective kernel width beyond physical one improving generalization capabilities against complex patterns seen rarely under standard kernels alone

